20Underway%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20South%20Korean%20vlogger%20has%20courted%20controversy%20after%20claiming%20that%20she%20terminated%20her%20pregnancy%20at%20nine%20months.%20According%20to%20%3Cem%3ECNN%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20woman%2C%20whose%20identity%20hasn't%20been%20revealed%2C%20is%20being%20investigated%20for%20murder%20in%20a%20case%20that%20has%20prompted%20horror%20in%20South%20Korea.%20The%20case%20has%20raised%20urgent%20questions%20about%20the%20abortion%20laws%20in%20South%20Korea%20as%20there%20are%20no%20laws%20governing%20when%2C%20where%2C%20or%20how%20abortions%20can%20take%20place.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noindex%2C%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2024%2F09%2F20%2Fasia%2Fsouth-korea-abortion-youtube-video-intl-hnk%2Findex.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECNN%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Seoul%20National%20Police%20began%20investigating%20the%20woman%20in%20July%20at%20the%20request%20of%20the%20South%20Korean%20government%20after%20she%20posted%20a%20video%20to%20YouTube%20purportedly%20documenting%20her%20experience%20of%20getting%20an%20abortion%2C%20cops%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20abortions%20past%2024%20weeks%20are%20banned%20in%20many%20jurisdictions%2C%20or%20reserved%20for%20very%20exceptional%20cases.%20However%2C%20in%20South%20Korea%2C%20there%20are%20no%20laws%20governing%20when%2C%20where%20or%20how%20abortions%20can%20take%20place.%20But%20this%20was%20not%20always%20the%20case.%20For%20the%20last%20four%20years%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20policy%20vacuum.%20Before%20this%2C%20strict%20laws%20governing%20the%20medical%20procedure%20made%20abortion%20a%20crime%20punishable%20by%20up%20to%20two%20years%20in%20prison.%20It%20only%20limited%20exceptions%20for%20rape%2C%20incest%2C%20and%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20life%2C%20health%20of%20the%20mother%20or%20the%20baby.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20in%202019%20that%20South%20Korea's%20Constitutional%20Court%20overturned%20the%20ban%2C%20giving%20the%20National%20Assembly%20until%20the%20end%20of%202020%20to%20enact%20new%20abortion%20laws%2C%20which%20the%20court%20recommended%20should%20include%20a%20term%20limit%20of%2022%20weeks.%20When%20the%20legislature%20failed%20to%20meet%20that%20deadline%2C%20the%20criminal%20provisions%20around%20abortion%20expired%2C%20effectively%20legalising%20abortion%20at%20any%20stage%20of%20pregnancy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fplease-forgive-me-elon-musk-after-billionaire-vinod-khosla-demands-apology-for-spreading-false-claims-6646580%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BPlease%20Forgive%20Me%26quot%3B%3A%20Elon%20Musk%20After%20Billionaire%20Vinod%20Khosla%20Demands%20Apology%20For%20Spreading%20False%20Claims%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20in%20a%20statement%20posted%20to%20its%20website%2C%20South%20Korea's%20Ministry%20of%20Justice%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20direction%2C%20details%2C%20and%20timing%20of%20the%20revision%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20country's%20abortion%20laws%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20decided%2C%20and%20that%20it%20needs%20to%20consult%20with%20the%20Health%20and%20Welfare%20Ministry%20-%20which%20oversees%20the%20Maternal%20and%20Child%20Health%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Ministry%20of%20Justice%20will%20do%20its%20best%20to%20discuss%20the%20issue%20so%20that%20the%20right%20to%20life%20of%20the%20fetus%2C%20and%20the%20right%20to%20health%20and%20the%20right%20to%20self-determination%20of%20the%20pregnant%20woman%20can%20be%20harmonised%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20policy%20vacuum%20experts%20say%20not%20only%20opens%20the%20door%20to%20potential%20malpractice%20but%20also%20hinders%20access%20to%20safe%20abortions.%20By%20not%20passing%20abortion%20laws%2C%20the%20National%20Assembly%20is%20%26quot%3Bnot%20doing%20its%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Cho%20Hee-kyoung%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20Hongik%20University%20in%20Seoul.%20%26quot%3BIf%20there%20is%20no%20law%20criminalizing%20a%20conduct%2C%20then%20there%20is%20no%20crime%20for%20carrying%20out%20that%20conduct%2C%26quot%3B%20Cho%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExperts%20also%20say%20that%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20clear%20regulations%2C%20women%20and%20abortion%20providers%20currently%20operate%20in%20a%20grey%20area%20with%20little%20guidance%20as%20to%20what%20is%20permitted%20and%20what%20might%20break%20other%20laws.%20Credible%20information%20about%20where%20to%20get%20an%20abortion%20is%20hard%20to%20come%20by%2C%20and%20the%20procedure%20is%20not%20covered%20under%20the%20country's%20public%20health%20system%2C%20the%20outlet%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727269620000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Fijglfd0g_abortion-representational_625x300_15_August_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fs-korean-vlogger-claims-to-have-aborted-baby-at-9-months-probe-underway-6647828%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20South%20Korean%20vlogger%20has%20courted%20controversy%20after%20claiming%20that%20she%20terminated%20her%20pregnancy%20at%20nine%20months.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fs-korean-vlogger-claims-to-have-aborted-baby-at-9-months-probe-underway-6647828%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%222024%20Mahindra%20Thar%20Roxx%204x4%20Prices%20Revealed%3A%20Check%20Variant-Wise%20Pricing%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Mahindra%20Thar%20Roxx%20was%20recently%20launched%20in%20the%20country%2C%20and%20it%20is%20enjoying%20strong%20attention%20from%20the%20off-roading%20community.%20Sadly%2C%20the%20brand%20had%20been%20tight-lipped%20about%20the%20prices%20of%20the%204x4%20variants%20until%20now.%20However%2C%20the%20prices%20are%20now%20revealed%2C%20with%20an%20in